title: "ITU and Finance & Economics: A Single-Axiom View of Banking, Markets, Cryptocurrency, Macroeconomics, Quantitative Finance, AI Finance, Regulation, and Inequality — Pass-1 Extension Paper #12, Block D 4/5"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; Tier 0 v3.0 at
  10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to finance and economics. Tier 1 paper
  #42, twelfth paper of Pass-1 extension, Block D 4/5 = 80% (after
  #39 Manufacturing + #40 Transportation + #41 Agriculture).
  Introduces K_finance across 8 sub-states (banking, markets,
  crypto, macro, quant, AI, regulation, inequality). ITU axiom
  delta S = delta <K> verified to machine precision in 11 contexts.
  42-vertex ITU polytope.
  Theoretical position: Finance = K-state economic information
  processing. Markets = K-state aggregation (Hayek). Crypto =
  K-state cryptographic alternative. AI finance = K-state
  computational acceleration.
  Key results: BC 3000 Mesopotamia clay ledgers, BC 700 Lydia
  coins, 1397 Medici Bank, 1602 VOC first stock company, 1694 Bank
  of England, 1776 Smith Wealth of Nations, 1913 Federal Reserve,
  1944 Bretton Woods, 1971 Nixon Shock, 1973 Black-Scholes (Nobel
  1997 Merton-Scholes), 1987 Black Monday, 2008.9.15 Lehman
  Brothers ($691B largest bankruptcy), 2009.1.3 Bitcoin genesis,
  2020 COVID, 2022 inflation. Global 2024: GDP $110T, debt $315T
  (286%).
  Banking: BoE 1694, BOJ 1882, Fed 1913 (dual mandate 1977), ECB
  1998, Fed peak balance $9T (2022), QE eras + Pandemic $4.5T,
  US CPI peak 9.1% (2022.6), Fed 0%->5.50% fastest hiking, BOJ
  NIRP end 2024.3 (8 yr), SVB 2023.3 ($209B 2nd largest US),
  Credit Suisse -> UBS 2023, Draghi "Whatever it takes" 2012.7.26.
  Markets: Amsterdam 1602 first stock, NYSE 1792, NASDAQ 1971
  first electronic, NYSE $28T #1, Magnificent 7 $17.2T total
  (NVIDIA $3.4T 1T->3T 18mo, Apple $3.5T, Microsoft $3.2T), Nikkei
  42K+ 2024.7 (34 yr high), US Treasury $35T (debt/GDP 122%),
  global bond market $140T, SPDR S&P 500 first ETF 1993, ETF $11T
  (2024), Bitcoin spot ETFs 2024.1.10 ($100B+ AUM by 2024.12, IBIT
  $40B), passive 50%+ US AUM.
  Crypto: Satoshi 2008.10.31 whitepaper, 2009.1.3 genesis,
  2010.5.22 Pizza Day (10K BTC), halving cycles (50->25->12.5->
  6.25->3.125 BTC 2024.4), 21M supply cap, Bitcoin $100K 2024.12
  (first time), Trump Nashville Bitcoin Conference 2024.7,
  Buterin Ethereum 2015.7.30 mainnet (age 19 whitepaper), The
  Merge PoS 2022.9.15 (energy -99.95%), Dencun 2024.4, DeFi TVL
  peak $180B 2021, Tether $130B (USDT 2014), UST/Luna collapse
  2022 $40B, FTX collapse 2022.11 -> SBF 25 yr (2024.3), crypto
  market cap $3.5T (2024.12), China DCEP $250B+, Trump 2024.11
  win -> BTC $69K->$93K, Worldcoin (Altman) 6.5M users.
  Macroeconomics: Smith 1776, Marx 1867, Keynes General Theory
  1936 (aggregate demand, multiplier 1/(1-MPC)), Friedman
  monetarism Nobel 1976, Krugman Nobel 2008 (new trade theory),
  Kahneman Nobel 2002 (Prospect 1979 Tversky), Thaler Nudge
  (Nobel 2017), Acemoglu+Johnson+Robinson Nobel Economics 2024
  (institutions, Why Nations Fail), Goldin Nobel 2023 (women
  labor), MMT Kelton 2020, Bernanke+Diamond+Dybvig Nobel 2022
  (banking).
  Quantitative Finance: Bachelier 1900 thesis (Brownian motion
  5 yr pre-Einstein), Markowitz Portfolio 1952 (Nobel 1990),
  Sharpe CAPM 1964, Fama EMH 1965 (Nobel 2013), Black-Scholes
  1973 (Merton-Scholes Nobel 1997, derivatives $640T BIS 2023),
  Engle GARCH 1986 (Nobel 2003), VIX 1993, Jim Simons Renaissance
  Tech 1982 Medallion ~39% annual (1988-2018 greatest hedge),
  Simons died 2024 ($31B + $5B donated). AI Finance: Renaissance
  ML pioneer 1990s, 2010 Flash Crash, Bloomberg GPT 2023 (50B
  params), JPMorgan IndexGPT 2024, Morgan Stanley AI @ MS,
  robo-advisors $300B+ (Vanguard PA, Betterment + Wealthfront $50B
  each), HFT 50%+ US equity.
  Regulation + Crises: 1933 Glass-Steagall + SEC 1934, 1999
  Gramm-Leach-Bliley (G-S repeal), 2010.7 Dodd-Frank (848 pages),
  Basel III (Tier 1 6%), EU MiCA 2024, DORA 2025. Frauds: Enron
  $74B 2001, WorldCom $11B, Madoff $65B Ponzi 2008, LIBOR $9B,
  Wells Fargo, FTX $32B. Inequality: Piketty Capital 21c 2013 (1.5M
  English copies, r > g), 2024 WIR Top 10% own 76% wealth + Top 1%
  38%, US top 1% income 9% (1980) -> 22% (2024), Milanovic
  Elephant Curve, Worldcoin 6.5M, Stiglitz Nobel 2001.
  Ten falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.765; Strong/Medium/Weak =
  6/4/0) including LLM finance major IB standard 2027 (P=0.90,
  Strong), AI trading 70%+ major markets 2027 (P=0.85, Strong),
  AI macro forecasting standard 2028 (P=0.85, Strong), EU MiCA full
  enforcement 2026 (P=0.90, Strong), passive 60%+ US AUM 2027
  (P=0.85, Strong), stablecoin major bank issued 2027 (P=0.80,
  Strong), CBDC 30+ countries launch 2030 (P=0.75, Medium), Bitcoin
  $150K 2026 (P=0.55, Medium), AI productivity benefits top 1% 2030
  (P=0.65, Medium), AI alpha collapses efficiency 2030 (P=0.55,
  Medium). Block D 4/5 = 80%. Pass-1 extension 12/15 = 80% (4/5
  surpassed). Pass-1 interpretive synthesis.
